    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1889-02-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1889-02-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="233"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d233">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mutsu</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Japan</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1889-02-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 11, 1889</date>. (Received February
                        11.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have just received the following telegram from
                    Count Okuma: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The constitution of the Empire was proclaimed by His Majesty in person
                            this morning amidst great enthusiasm of the people.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>I hasten to communicate this important news, feeling assured that you will hear
                    it with interest, and that His Majesty the Emperor and the Government and people
                    of Japan will have, at this important epoch in the history of the Empire, the
                    best wishes of your Government and of the people of the United States.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">M. Mutsu.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
